parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including stalling, loss of power, and failure of essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The cruise control light comes on without being selected
the heating/cooling system fails to operate
the fuel gauge does not register correctly
the vehicle stalls or loses power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes lodged in the ignition switch
the ignition switch fails to turn
and the vehicle stalls without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the security system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, which can lead to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: and the anti-theft system engages and shuts down the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various malfunctions, including electrical system failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power windows fail to operate
and the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Passlock system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, which can lead to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The Passlock system fails to recognize the key
and the security light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a fire. This can also lead to costly repairs and potentially leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident. This can also lead to costly repairs and potentially leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaking into Cooling System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil system can cause oil to leak into the cooling system, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a fire. This can also lead to costly repairs and potentially leave the driver stranded.
The stalling of the engine can cause a loss of power and potentially lead to an accident. This can also leave the driver stranded.
The failure of headlights and turn signals can cause accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions, and may lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Headlights and turn signals fail to function
sometimes accompanied by a sudden loss of pressure or sticking of the switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hazard light switch can cause accidents, especially when turning or changing lanes, and may lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Turn signals and hazard lights fail to function
or require repeated pressing of the switch to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line corrosion can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS and Traction Control System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS and traction control system malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: ABS and traction control warning lights illuminate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rotor warping and premature wear can cause the vehicle to vibrate when braking, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
Brake pedal pulsation and vibration can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents.
